{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17499323","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17499323"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T09:58:37+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T09:58:37+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1485"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1485","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1485"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.45,0.22,0.05,0.1,0.18]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1485"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"109658"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1485","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1485"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1485"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"92061"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"31"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"377"},{"type":"tags","id":"4985"},{"type":"tags","id":"8088"},{"type":"tags","id":"11634"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"3622"},{"type":"contributions","id":"4385"},{"type":"contributions","id":"13341"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26179"},{"type":"contributions","id":"34446"},{"type":"contributions","id":"36525"},{"type":"contributions","id":"41104"},{"type":"contributions","id":"45067"},{"type":"contributions","id":"47253"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"109658","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/109658"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 45-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic concerned about her breasts being \u0022uneven\u0022. She noticed this four months ago and feels it has progressively worsened. She has two children aged 12 and 10 years whom she breastfed. She uses a levonorgestrel intrauterine device for contraception. Her menarche was at age 12, and she experiences occasional bleeding every one to two months with her intrauterine device.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EShe has no known family history of medical conditions. Her medical history includes hypertension, pre-diabetes and obesity. Her only medication is perindopril. She has no allergies.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, she appears well. Her pulse rate is 76/min, blood pressure 130/95 mmHg, respiratory rate 16/min, SpO2 98% on room air, and temperature 36.8\u00b0C. Her BMI is 32 kg/m2. The initial inspection of her breasts is shown (Image).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Carcinoma of the right breast","Carcinoma of the left breast","Paget disease of the right nipple","Paget disease of the left nipple","Cystosarcoma phyllodes of the left breast"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe image shows retraction and loss of normal contour of the right breast. This distortion will become more pronounced when the patient raises her arms. Such contraction typically indicates an underlying infiltrating tumour, making \u003Cstrong\u003Ecarcinoma of the right breast\u003C/strong\u003E the most likely diagnosis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eleft breast\u003C/strong\u003E appears normal without contraction or visible masses, making carcinoma of the left breast unlikely.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPaget disease of the right nipple\u003C/strong\u003E and \u003Cstrong\u003EPaget disease of the left nipple\u003C/strong\u003E can be excluded as both nipples appear normal. Paget disease characteristically presents with nipple changes including scaling, redness, flattening, ulceration, and sometimes discharge. It is often mistaken for nipple eczema and requires punch biopsy for definitive diagnosis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECystosarcoma phyllodes\u003C/strong\u003E (now termed phyllodes tumour) is a rare fibroepithelial neoplasm characterised by a leaf-like growth pattern. While it can be benign or malignant, it typically presents as a discrete mass rather than causing breast contraction. These tumours arise from breast stromal tissue and can resemble fibroadenomas clinically.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Retraction or distortion of breast contour may indicate underlying breast carcinoma","Breast asymmetry that develops over months requires urgent investigation","Paget disease of the breast presents with nipple changes including scaling, redness, and ulceration"],"references":["National Cancer Institute, 2012. Paget Disease of the Breast. Access at: https://www.cancer.gov/types/breast/paget-breast-fact-sheet.","Breast Cancer Org, 2019. Phyllodes Tumors of the Breast. Access at: https://www.breastcancer.org/symptoms/types/phyllodes."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"92061"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1485"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"12172"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"12172","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/12172"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/7016083a-bad0-4a96-aef1-5b6b545a9b86.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/7016083a-bad0-4a96-aef1-5b6b545a9b86.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":587,"height":440}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"92061","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/92061"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-07-24T09:03:04+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-07-24T09:03:44+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1485"}},"content":{"data":{"ty